(86, 1, '2024-02-11 00:22:53', '2024-02-11 00:22:53', 'Welcome! My name is Don Sijo, and I\'m a passionate web developer originally from Kerala, India, currently pursuing my studies at Georgian College in Canada. As I immerse myself in the vibrant field of web development, I find myself constantly inspired by the endless possibilities and creative challenges it presents.\r\n\r\nMy journey into the world of web development began with a spark of curiosity and a desire to explore the digital landscape. At Georgian College, I\'m currently enrolled in the Interactive Media Design program, where I\'m focusing on honing my skills in web development. Through hands-on projects and coursework, I\'ve delved into various programming languages, including C, C++, C#, Python, and PHP. Additionally, I\'ve developed a strong foundation in front-end development, mastering HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, while also exploring the intricacies of user experience design with tools like Illustrator.\r\n\r\nOne of the highlights of my academic journey has been the creation of my personal portfolio website from scratch. This project allowed me to apply my knowledge and skills in a practical setting, resulting in a platform that showcases my projects, experiences, and capabilities as a web developer. It\'s a testament to my dedication to continuous learning and my passion for delivering high-quality digital solutions.\r\n\r\nLooking ahead, I\'m excited about the prospect of translating my skills and experiences into meaningful contributions within the web development industry. Whether it\'s collaborating with like-minded individuals on innovative projects or pushing the boundaries of what\'s possible in the digital realm, I\'m committed to making a positive impact through my work.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-159\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/ccb7ffcc-a79f-4024-a508-e4ff9509b843.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"528\" height=\"528\" />', 'About me', ''